<subSubSection id="059EB800CD4064BB3DC658ACCDD9FBCD" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="characterization">
<paragraph id="F20B7E752E15E99BDF46C24B1E566C0B" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Characterization.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1869CF9CD1E1211B047B1F86C4A59144" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Shell H/L ratio about 1.04. W/H ratio approximately 0.86. Muscle scars rarely visible; anterior adductor scar 2/3 of posterior scar. Anterior and posterior parts of the hinge plate usually of same length. Width of posterior row of teeth occupies about 65% of width of hinge plate, which is thin for its size (whp/H approximately 0.07). Posterior part of the hinge plate longer than anterior one. Prodissoconch smooth, with length approximately 120 
<normalizedToken id="B6F6F16021E89CFA6EB6C8A0F755A2D2" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="92E6AAA32D761DCEC618CC70913903B5" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="078C387DB2CADCE633BAEEE80AB6AB00" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF8192D588FBFFECA40A62EBA27049E5" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
This species was recently well described and for this reason we add only new information on the proportions of the shell (H/L and width) and hinge plate characteristics. 
<bibRefCitation id="713E5903928BA1CC8248A38149A0BBDE" author="Sanders, HL" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="237 - 261" title="Studies on the deep sea Protobranchia (Bivalvia): Prologue and the Pristiglomidae." volume="145" year="1973">Sanders and Allen (1973)</bibRefCitation>
noted no evident muscle scars or pallial line. In the Campos Basin specimens, no pallial line is discernible on the valves, but faint muscle scars are apparent in some specimens. It is a common species in the Atlantic, and its occurrence in the Campos Basin was expected, since it was previously recorded from the northern Brazilian coast (Pernambuco) and from Argentina. The present study provides new points to the geographical distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="72B8C025B6D0C431DE50FD34FC4A0183" class="Bivalvia" family="Pristiglomidae" genus="Pristigloma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pristigloma alba" order="Nuculanida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="alba">Pristigloma alba</taxonomicName>
, and is also the shallowest (1200 m) record for the species, which was previously known only from abyssal depths (2100-4898 m).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
